      <hedline>
        <hl1>Tales From Aloft</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: In response to your  article about plastic, nonidentifiable airline food, ''Indigestible Flying Objects'' (June 25), may I suggest a good alternative? Put in an order for kosher food, coming and going. The kosher caterers are very careful in preparation, give nice portions, and the food is tasty too. My only objection is the white rolls. I'd love onion, rye or pumpernickel.</p>
        <p>MARION SAULIG  New York, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
